&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancy: 1.5 wte Senior Specialist Dietitians Neurosciences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time and Part Time &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for band 7 senior specialist Dietitians at Leeds Teaching Hospitals. These posts will be the clinical leads for the neurosurgery and neuro rehabilitation pathway&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based at Leeds General Infirmary and Chapel Allerton Hospital you will work alongside the multidisciplinary team on our neurosurgery and specialist neuro rehabilitation wards.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also work closely with dietetic colleagues in neuro critical care and stroke to provide an integrated dietetic service across these specialities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be supported by band 5 and 6 dietitians and will have line management responsibilities. In addition you will work with a band 3 dietetic assistant on our neuro rehabilitation unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for dietitians with excellent clinical skills and experience in leadership to take on these exciting and challenging roles. The posts could be split into a lead for acute services and a lead for neuro rehabilitation depending on the skills and interests of the candidates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be actively involved in the development, implementation and audit of patient care practices as part of the Clinical Governance assurance framework.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The posts offer excellent opportunities for professional and personal development as the clinical services evolve.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The department is involved in student training and committed to CPD.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additionally, as a senior member of the dietetic team you will take an active part in the provision of training programmes for A, B and C Dietetic Students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Trust values are that we are patient-centred, empowered, collaborative, fair and accountable. If your values match ours we would love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a strong focus on investing in the continued professional development of our people to ensure that they can achieve their full potential. We lead the way in providing further training and career development opportunities in every department and at every level of our organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a culture where people take a real pride in their work, respect each other and all work together to deliver the most exceptional standards of patient care. We have a happy, productive work environment where everyone in every role plays their own important part in our success. Click on the attached links to take a closer look at how a career with us could deliver the work environment, progression opportunities, rewards, benefits and training you want from your NHS career in Leeds&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please do not hesitate to contact Lynn George Clinical Dietetic Manager on 0113 2065868 or by e-mail &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lynn.george3@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; to discuss these posts further&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
